# Frontend Rules

> Frontend (client) rules. Project-wide rules live in `.cursor/rules/core/`.
> Server (backend) rules: `.cursor/rules/backend/`.

**Stack:** Next.js (App Router) · FSD · React Query · Axios · next-intl

## Rule Files

When working on frontend code, follow **core** rules plus **all** rules in this folder:

| File               | Scope                                                    |
| ------------------ | -------------------------------------------------------- |
| `core.mdc`         | FSD public API, imports, exports, i18n                   |
| `architecture.mdc` | FSD layers, Next.js integration, server code, navigation |
| `api.mdc`          | API paths/keys, React Query, cache, mutations            |

## Priority

`api.mdc` > `architecture.mdc` > `core.mdc` > `.cursor/rules/core/*`

## Client Scope (`apps/client`)

```
apps/client/
├── app/          # Next.js App Router
├── pages/        # Pages Router stub
└── src/          # FSD layers (incl. shared/lib/i18n for translations)
```

## Checklist

Before finishing a frontend task, verify:

### FSD & structure (`core.mdc`, `architecture.mdc`)

- [ ] Code is in the correct FSD layer and slice
- [ ] Slice has root `index.ts` public API
- [ ] Imports follow FSD layer direction and public API rules
- [ ] Server code in `api/server/` subfolder
- [ ] Navigation paths use `navigationMap`
- [ ] Root `app/` page is a thin re-export from `src/pages/`
- [ ] Root `pages/README.md` stub is present

### Conventions (`core.mdc`)

- [ ] Types in `types.ts`; constants in `model/constants.ts` or `api/constants.ts`
- [ ] Named exports only (except `page.tsx` / `layout.tsx`)
- [ ] Checked `shared/` before creating new utilities or UI
- [ ] No hardcoded user-facing text (see `architecture.mdc`)

### API & data (`api.mdc`)

- [ ] Paths and keys in `shared/model/api.ts` (`API_PATHS`, `API_KEYS`)
- [ ] Pure request functions in `api/requests.ts`
- [ ] Client hooks in `api/client/`, server actions in `api/server/`
- [ ] Cache utilities in entity `lib/cache.ts`
- [ ] Pages handle loading and error states for `use*Query`
- [ ] Async mutations wrapped in `try/catch`
